Key questions

Busiest days of the week

In [60]:
busiest_days = df['orders_day_of_week'].value_counts().plot.bar(rot = 'horizontal', color = 'gray', xlabel = 'day of the week', ylabel = 'orders (in tens of millions)', title= 'Orders per day')

Most orders are placed on weekends, with Saturday being the busiest day. Least orders are placed on Wednesday.

Busiest hours of the day

In [61]:
busiest_hours = df['order_hour_of_day'].value_counts().plot.bar(rot = 'horizontal', color = 'gray', xlabel = 'hour of the day', ylabel = 'orders (in tens of millions)', title= 'Orders per hour')
In [63]:
sctpl_time = sns.scatterplot(x = 'orders_day_of_week', y = 'order_hour_of_day', data = df, color = 'gray')

Most order are placed between 9 a.m. and 4 p.m. with 10-11 a.m. being the busiest period of the day. Least order are between midnight and 6 a.m.

gender_dep = pd.crosstab(df['department_id'], df['gender']).plot.bar(figsize = (20,7), rot = 'horizontal', color = ['gray', 'darkgray'], xlabel = 'department', ylabel = 'orders (in tens of millions)', title='Department popularity by gender')

Most of our customers fall into two categories:

  • 23 - middle-aged adult, married, parent, middle income
  • 35 - older adult, married, parent, middle income

Popularity of certain departments is more affected by customer's income than by their gender, family/marital status or number of dependants. There are also regional differences.

In [110]:
price_dspo_mean = df.groupby(['profile_category']).agg({'prices': ['mean'], 'days_since_prior_order': ['mean']}).plot.bar(figsize = (30,6), color = ['gray', 'lightgray'], rot = 'horizontal', xlabel = 'profile category', ylabel='prices & ordering frequency', title='Order prices and order frequency by profile category', legend=False)

On average, the profile category 06 (young, single, parent, upper income) orders most often, while paying more per order than most groups. On the contrast, profile category 25 (older, single, nonparent, low income) pays the least per order, while ordering less than most groups.
